*Hobbit* (hobbit@elf.com) wrote:
> [someone else wrote:]
>    Has there been any contacts with the anonymous remailer owner about trying
>    to get logs of who possibiliy could have sent that?

> Would *you* use an "anonymous" remailer that you knew kept LOGS of its
> transactions?!  Not likely.

On the other hand, would you use an anonymous remailer for something
really sensitive, and not take precautions in case the remailer operator
*is* keeping logs that could be subpoenaed?  Chaining remailers will
help, especially cross-jurisdiction or cross-border chaining.


Rich

